	spa: program download

SPA.R takes allelic data and formats it for --gfile format in the spa analysis.
--gfile format replaces allelic data with 0-2 for the number of minor alleles. Barley is treated as a haploid, with a 0 for no minor alleles, and 1 for one minor allele.

Spa_input.df is the output of SPA.R.

To run spa analysis:
# -k 3: samples from around the world
# -n 2: 2 origins

spa --gfile Spa_input.df --location-output Spa_input.df --model-output Spa_input.model

#known.loc: known geographnical locations
spa --gfile Spa_input.df --location-imput known.loc --model-output myfile.model
